		{
			"name": "Email Operations",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Send Bulk Emails",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
					"    const response = pm.response.json();",
					"    console.log(\"Emails sent successfully!\");",
					"    console.log(\"Sent:\", response.sent);",
					"    console.log(\"Failed:\", response.failed);",
					"    console.log(\"Total:\", response.total);",
					"    if (response.errors && response.errors.length > 0) {",
					"        console.log(\"Errors:\", response.errors);",
					"    }",
					"} else {",
					"    console.log(\"Error:\", pm.response.json());",
					"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"subject\": \"{{emailSubject}}\",\n    \"recipients\": [\n        \"recipient1@example.com\",\n        \"recipient2@example.com\"\n    ],\n    \"templateId\": \"{{templateId}}\",\n    \"html\": null,\n    \"smtpId\": null,\n    \"projectId\": \"{{projectId}}\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": {
									"language": "json"
								}
							}
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/emails/send-bulk",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"api",
								"emails",
								"send-bulk"
							]
						},
						"description": "Send bulk emails to multiple recipients using a template or custom HTML.\n\n## Request Body Parameters\n\n### Required:\n- `subject` (string): Email subject line\n- `recipients` (array): Array of recipient email addresses\n\n### Optional:\n- `templateId` (string): Template ID to use. Can be MongoDB ObjectId or custom template ID. If not provided, uses project default template.\n- `html` (string): Custom HTML content. Either `templateId` or `html` must be provided.\n- `smtpId` (string): SMTP configuration ID to use. If not provided, uses project default SMTP.\n- `projectId` (string): Project ID. Required for API key authentication (must match the API key's project).\n\n## Notes\n- If both `templateId` and `html` are provided, `html` will override the template content.\n- If `templateId` is a custom template ID (not MongoDB ObjectId format), it will be searched by `customTemplateId` field.\n- Emails are sent in batches of 10 with a 1-second delay between batches to avoid rate limiting.\n- The response includes progress information and any errors encountered."
					},
